From: bot <bot@example.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 08:48:36 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Use the real struct timespec with the UCRT

cdf.h maps struct timespec to winsock2's struct timeval on WIN32, whose
members are 32-bit longs. cdf_ctime takes a const time_t * (64-bit on
Windows), so passing &ts.tv_sec does not compile with that mapping. The
UCRT has a C11-conforming struct timespec with a time_t tv_sec, so only
apply the timeval fallback for toolchains that lack it.
---
 src/cdf.h | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/cdf.h b/src/cdf.h
index 6dddb3d..5c1b797 100644
--- a/src/cdf.h
+++ b/src/cdf.h
@@ -37,9 +37,13 @@
 
 #ifdef WIN32
 #include <winsock2.h>
+#ifndef _MSC_VER
+/* The UCRT provides a C11 struct timespec (with 64-bit time_t); only
+   map it to struct timeval for old toolchains that lack it. */
 #define timespec timeval
 #define tv_nsec tv_usec
 #endif
+#endif
 #ifdef __DJGPP__
 #define timespec timeval
 #define tv_nsec tv_usec
